article.headline: Wright St. 74, Ill.-Chicago 64 (OT)
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- DaShaun Wood scored 24 points to lead Wright State to a 74-64 overtime win over Illinois-Chicago on Wednesday night. Robert Bush hit a 3-pointer for UIC with 28 seconds left to tie it at 58. Wright State (18-8, 11-2 Horizon) had one final chance to win it in regulation, but Wood missed a jumper in the closing seconds. But after Wood hit a 3-pointer two minutes into overtime that put Wright State ahead 63-59, the Flames (19-6, 4-8) could not cut the lead to less than four down the stretch. Vaughn Duggins scored 13 points for Wright State, including seven in overtime. Drew Burleson added 13 points and seven rebounds for the Raiders. Othyus Jeffers led four UIC players in double figures with 14 points and 11 rebounds. Jovan Stefanov and Josh Mayo scored 13 points apiece, and Robert Bush added 10 for the Flames. UIC outrebounded the Raiders 48-42, but were outscored by Wright State in the paint 34-24. The Raiders also shot 40.3 percent from the field, to 32.4 percent for UIC. The game had 17 ties and 12 lead changes.
